Oh right, because the class literal User[].class is accessible, unlike parameterized types which require TypeToken. So the missing code is using gson.fromJson with the jsonList string and the User array class. So the line should be:

User [] usersArray = gson.fromJson(jsonList, User[].class);

That would parse the JSON array into an array of User objects. Then the code can access usersArray[0].name correctly. Let me double-check. The jsonList is a JSON array of two user objects. Using User[].class as the second argument to fromJson should work. Yes, that makes sense.
